@@ -0,0 +1,99 @@
+# cosmic-comp — kinetic scroll branch
+
+This branch adds compositor-side kinetic ("fling") scrolling and per-app
+scroll-factor overrides to the COSMIC Wayland compositor.
+
+## Compile and install
+
+### 1. Install Rust (if you don't already have it)
+
+```sh
+curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh
+. "$HOME/.cargo/env"
+```
+
+### 2. Install build dependencies (Debian/Ubuntu/Pop!\_OS)
+
+```sh
+sudo apt install -y libudev-dev libsystemd-dev libseat-dev \
+    libdisplay-info-dev libwayland-dev libxkbcommon-dev \
+    libinput-dev libpixman-1-dev libgbm-dev
+```
+
+### 3. Build
+
+```sh
+cargo build --release -p cosmic-comp
+```
+
+Takes ~5 min with LTO. Output: `target/release/cosmic-comp` (~33 MB).
+
+### 4. Back up the existing binary and install the new one
+
+```sh
+sudo cp /usr/bin/cosmic-comp /usr/bin/cosmic-comp.bak
+sudo install -Dm0755 target/release/cosmic-comp /usr/bin/cosmic-comp
+```
+
+Rollback at any time:
+
+```sh
+sudo cp /usr/bin/cosmic-comp.bak /usr/bin/cosmic-comp
+# or
+sudo apt install --reinstall cosmic-comp
+```
+
+### 5. Configure (see below), then log out and log back in
+
+The new binary loads on the next session start. There is no live reload.
+
+## Configuration
+
+Edit `~/.config/cosmic/com.system76.CosmicComp/v1/input_touchpad`. The new
+fields are `kinetic` and `scroll_factor_per_app` on `ScrollConfig`. Both
+are optional and default to off / empty.
+
+Example (copy of a working config):
+
+```ron
+(
+    state: Enabled,
+    click_method: Some(Clickfinger),
+    scroll_config: Some((
+        method: Some(TwoFinger),
+        natural_scroll: Some(true),
+        scroll_button: None,
+        scroll_factor: Some(1.0),
+        kinetic: Some(true),
+        scroll_factor_per_app: Some({
+            "firefox": 0.135,
+            "brave-browser": 0.15,
+            "jetbrains-rider": 0.24,
+        }),
+    )),
+    tap_config: Some((
+        enabled: true,
+        button_map: Some(LeftRightMiddle),
+        drag: true,
+        drag_lock: false,
+    )),
+)
+```
+
+- `kinetic: Some(true)` enables inertial fling on two-finger scroll.
+- `scroll_factor` is the device-level multiplier (1.0 = libinput default).
+- `scroll_factor_per_app` keys are `xdg_toplevel.app_id` (Wayland) or
+  `WM_CLASS` class (XWayland); values multiply the device factor for that
+  app.
+
+### Finding an app's identifier
+
+The compositor logs the resolved app_id on every axis event.
+
+After relog, scroll inside the app and:
+
+```sh
+journalctl --user -f | grep "scroll axis"
+```
+
+Use the `app_id=` string verbatim as the key in `scroll_factor_per_app`.
